1
00:00:00,810 --> 00:00:03,020
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:03,020 --> 00:00:08,110
During the battle surrounding Nirvana 
with Oracion Seis, Erza fell.

3
00:00:08,110 --> 00:00:11,060
And then we lost Lyon...

4
00:00:11,060 --> 00:00:16,200
We managed to take back the 
kidnapped Wendy, however...

5
00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:19,250
Why is Jellal here, too?

6
00:00:20,680 --> 00:00:28,670
If it's love and dreams and you it'll become magical.

7
00:00:28,670 --> 00:00:35,840
Now, let's cast a smile spell!

8
00:00:43,460 --> 00:00:48,770
I kind of admired this powerful world,

9
00:00:48,770 --> 00:00:53,190
chock-full of problems.

10
00:00:54,110 --> 00:00:59,970
Frozen time has started to move again

11
00:00:59,970 --> 00:01:05,580
ever since I met you.

12
00:01:05,580 --> 00:01:11,000
Why were we born? Why do we live?

13
00:01:11,000 --> 00:01:16,840
I don't need any complicated answers.

14
00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:22,780
Laugh! Cry! Be honest with yourself.

15
00:01:22,780 --> 00:01:27,560
Simple feelings are the most important.

16
00:01:27,560 --> 00:01:35,900
You can change those tears shed on sad nights into strength.

17
00:01:35,900 --> 00:01:42,530
Now, let's cast a smile spell!

18
00:02:01,670 --> 00:02:02,900
That sound...

19
00:02:03,310 --> 00:02:04,720
Hey, Happy!

20
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:47,680
Darkness.

21
00:02:58,420 --> 00:02:59,290
Lyon...

22
00:03:00,380 --> 00:03:04,200
N-No... Lyon-sama has...

23
00:03:04,490 --> 00:03:06,750
There's no way that guy's dead!

24
00:03:06,750 --> 00:03:07,660
Let's search for him!

25
00:03:08,230 --> 00:03:09,180
Come on!

26
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,470
Why?

27
00:03:17,920 --> 00:03:19,360
Why did Lyon-sama have to...

28
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:26,750
Who is to blame?

29
00:03:32,330 --> 00:03:35,900
I know you are here. Show yourself.

30
00:03:40,850 --> 00:03:43,750
As expected from one of the 
Ten Great Wizard Saints.

31
00:03:44,110 --> 00:03:45,060
Yes!

32
00:03:59,100 --> 00:04:02,290
My magic softens the earth.

33
00:04:02,290 --> 00:04:05,480
And your magic hardens the earth!

34
00:04:05,790 --> 00:04:06,680
Yes!

35
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:12,680
So then, which one is stronger, yes?

36
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:16,980
Naturally, it is not the 
superior magic that counts,

37
00:04:16,980 --> 00:04:18,860
but the one with the stronger ideals!

38
00:04:19,110 --> 00:04:20,620
That is not the case.

39
00:04:20,620 --> 00:04:23,210
The winner, since time immemorial,

40
00:04:23,210 --> 00:04:25,140
is the one with the money, yes!

41
00:04:37,710 --> 00:04:39,660
We're here!

42
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,100
Natsu!

43
00:04:41,450 --> 00:04:45,980
How'd this happen? Suddenly a map 
to this place popped into my head...

44
00:04:45,980 --> 00:04:48,270
Anyway, hurry and wake Wendy-chan...

45
00:04:48,270 --> 00:04:49,010
Oh, right.

46
00:04:50,220 --> 00:04:51,610
Wake up, Wendy!

47
00:04:51,610 --> 00:04:53,730
Please, save Erza!

48
00:04:53,730 --> 00:04:55,880
Calm down, Natsu!

49
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:07,360
I'm sorry! I...

50
00:05:13,060 --> 00:05:15,360
I don't care about that right now!

51
00:05:17,230 --> 00:05:19,680
Erza's been bitten by a poisonous snake.

52
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,540
Please save her! I'm begging you!

53
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:24,800
Poison?

54
00:05:31,420 --> 00:05:36,420
We need Erza-san's strength 
to fight Oracion Seis.

55
00:05:36,420 --> 00:05:39,320
Please, save Erza!

56
00:05:40,380 --> 00:05:41,410
Please!

57
00:05:44,120 --> 00:05:46,740
Of course! Yes, I'll do it!

58
00:05:47,880 --> 00:05:49,950
Thank goodness...

59
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:52,800
How long are you going to be splayed 
out like that? It's unbecoming...

60
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,040
Aye...

61
00:06:04,010 --> 00:06:08,260
I can't believe Jellal would do such 
a horrible thing to Erza-san...

62
00:06:13,590 --> 00:06:15,220
I can't believe it...

63
00:06:28,230 --> 00:06:32,340
Hmm... I can't hear this guy's thoughts.

64
00:06:33,130 --> 00:06:37,480
If only I could hear his thoughts, I 
wouldn't have to follow him like this.

65
00:06:40,420 --> 00:06:41,540
He stopped.

66
00:07:09,860 --> 00:07:11,600
Where the hell is this?

67
00:07:11,910 --> 00:07:13,950
There's a place like this in the Woodsea?

68
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:24,270
Could it be like Brain said? 
Is this where Nirvana...

69
00:07:45,480 --> 00:07:49,150
Finally we've found it! Our future!

70
00:07:52,190 --> 00:07:57,240
Finished. All the poison is 
gone from Erza-san's body.

71
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,270
And...?

72
00:08:05,540 --> 00:08:07,440
Y'alright!

73
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:09,210
Lucy, high-five!

74
00:08:09,210 --> 00:08:11,170
Thank goodness!

75
00:08:12,760 --> 00:08:14,550
Carla!

76
00:08:14,550 --> 00:08:15,930
Just this once.

77
00:08:15,930 --> 00:08:17,360
Aye!

78
00:08:17,360 --> 00:08:18,380
Wendy...

79
00:08:22,550 --> 00:08:23,850
Thanks.

80
00:08:27,100 --> 00:08:30,270
She might not wake up for a little while.

81
00:08:30,270 --> 00:08:32,280
But she'll be fine now.

82
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:35,950
Wow... Her complexion is returning to normal.

83
00:08:36,480 --> 00:08:38,140
So this is Sky Magic?

84
00:08:38,140 --> 00:08:39,160
You're too close!

85
00:08:39,430 --> 00:08:40,770
May I have a word?

86
00:08:40,770 --> 00:08:44,370
Please refrain from using 
Wendy's Sky Magic any more.

87
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:49,500
As you can see, it uses up a 
lot of Wendy's magic power.

88
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:51,680
Don't worry about me!

89
00:08:52,050 --> 00:08:53,510
Besides, I...

90
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:57,340
After Erza-san wakes up, it's 
time to launch a counterattack.

91
00:08:59,260 --> 00:09:01,760
Yeah! We'll K.O. those Oracion Seis!

92
00:09:02,010 --> 00:09:05,220
Yeah! We ain't gonna let 'em have Nirvana!

93
00:09:05,810 --> 00:09:07,020
What?

94
00:09:20,090 --> 00:09:22,590
A pillar of black light...

95
00:09:22,590 --> 00:09:23,670
Could that be...

96
00:09:28,460 --> 00:09:29,550
That's...

97
00:09:57,820 --> 00:10:00,500
That's... Nirvana!

98
00:10:15,820 --> 00:10:19,260
We've got it! We got it!

99
00:10:19,690 --> 00:10:23,500
It's... It's ours!

100
00:10:35,590 --> 00:10:37,900
What the heck is that light?

101
00:10:38,150 --> 00:10:41,680
Damn it... Could that be Nirvana?

102
00:11:40,330 --> 00:11:41,520
Father...

103
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:45,150
T-There is no mistaking it...

104
00:11:47,780 --> 00:11:49,470
Congratulations.

105
00:11:49,840 --> 00:11:53,360
Those guild wizards will all be wiped out...

106
00:11:53,700 --> 00:11:55,230
...before midnight.

107
00:11:57,050 --> 00:11:59,350
Father, you head toward that light.

108
00:11:59,350 --> 00:12:00,200
Yes.

109
00:12:03,250 --> 00:12:04,810
Is that Nirvana?

110
00:12:05,220 --> 00:12:08,700
So it was awakened by Oracion Seis first?

111
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:14,870
That light...

112
00:12:18,850 --> 00:12:20,340
Jellal is there!

113
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:23,050
Jellal?

114
00:12:28,650 --> 00:12:29,720
Natsu!

115
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:32,730
What do you mean, Jellal?

116
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:39,540
I-I... It's all my fault...

117
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:46,360
I can't let them meet!

118
00:12:47,630 --> 00:12:49,200
I can't let Erza see him!

119
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:54,010
I... will... crush him!

120
00:12:56,970 --> 00:12:58,250
Jellal?

121
00:13:02,300 --> 00:13:04,450
What could that light be?

122
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:05,390
Good question...

123
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:13,910
Look. Something is flowing out 
from that eerie "black tree."

124
00:13:14,430 --> 00:13:16,830
It's like it's being sucked into that light.

125
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:18,370
I wonder what it means?

126
00:13:20,170 --> 00:13:23,230
Maybe Nirvana is at the 
place where that light is!

127
00:13:24,150 --> 00:13:27,660
If that's the case, that means 
someone already found it!

128
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:31,500
Was it the alliance? Or Oracion Seis?

129
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:35,610
Hibiki, what's happening?

130
00:13:35,610 --> 00:13:37,660
Answer me, Hibiki!

131
00:13:39,160 --> 00:13:41,950
That magical power must be 
blocking communications.

132
00:13:42,740 --> 00:13:44,110
Damn it.

133
00:13:44,110 --> 00:13:47,020
I'll keep searching for Wendy!

134
00:13:47,020 --> 00:13:50,170
Understood. I'll head toward that light.

135
00:13:50,170 --> 00:13:51,250
Be careful!

136
00:13:54,350 --> 00:13:58,060
Damn it... What in the world is happening?

137
00:14:04,820 --> 00:14:07,150
Whose fault was it that Lyon-sama...

138
00:14:08,030 --> 00:14:10,450
Lyon!

139
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:14,120
Answer me, Lyon!

140
00:14:14,850 --> 00:14:16,010
Hey!

141
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:17,840
Lyon!

142
00:14:19,540 --> 00:14:21,080
His fault?

143
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:24,280
What in the world is that?

144
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:26,000
Nirvana.

145
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:26,900
Yes!

146
00:14:28,670 --> 00:14:30,880
Please, do not worry.

147
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:33,570
The main body has not yet started up.

148
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:36,560
That is only the seal being released.

149
00:14:36,560 --> 00:14:40,210
However, this definitely 
smells like money to me!

150
00:14:40,210 --> 00:14:41,140
Yes!

151
00:14:43,720 --> 00:14:46,570
There is no time to fight this guy, but...

152
00:14:47,100 --> 00:14:51,030
But the mission is to 
suppress Oracion Seis...

153
00:14:51,850 --> 00:14:55,240
Fight? Or stop Nirvana?

154
00:14:57,580 --> 00:14:59,700
Money! Money!

155
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:03,170
Now, we will become rich!

156
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,990
Now what?!

157
00:15:18,410 --> 00:15:20,010
We have to go after Natsu-kun!

158
00:15:20,010 --> 00:15:21,080
Natsu...

159
00:15:21,080 --> 00:15:23,060
Did he say something about Jellal?

160
00:15:23,060 --> 00:15:26,450
I'll explain later! We 
have to go after Natsu!

161
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:29,900
Erza is gone!

162
00:15:33,780 --> 00:15:35,870
What is with that girl?

163
00:15:35,870 --> 00:15:37,860
She didn't even thank Wendy!

164
00:15:37,860 --> 00:15:41,690
Erza... Maybe she heard 
the name Jellal, and...

165
00:15:41,690 --> 00:15:42,950
What'll we do?

166
00:15:43,950 --> 00:15:45,650
This is all my fault...

167
00:15:47,370 --> 00:15:55,970
Because I healed Jellal, they found 
Nirvana, and Erza-san and Natsu-san are...

168
00:16:02,930 --> 00:16:04,940
What do you think you're doing?!

169
00:16:09,950 --> 00:16:11,280
Jellal!

170
00:16:14,990 --> 00:16:19,490
We'll show you the power of 
Racer's personal guild, Harpyia!

171
00:16:19,490 --> 00:16:21,060
Get 'im!

172
00:16:22,370 --> 00:16:24,000
Outta my way!

173
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,770
Move it!

174
00:16:29,090 --> 00:16:31,630
I can't let him get near Erza!

175
00:16:31,890 --> 00:16:34,350
I can't let 'im!

176
00:16:37,210 --> 00:16:38,880
Sorry for shocking you.

177
00:16:38,880 --> 00:16:41,000
But all I did was knock her out.

178
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:43,560
But why? And why are we running?

179
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:45,840
We're heading after Natsu-kun and Erza-san!

180
00:16:45,840 --> 00:16:47,560
We'll head toward the light as well!

181
00:16:47,810 --> 00:16:49,540
I'm not buying it!

182
00:16:49,540 --> 00:16:53,700
I know Wendy's a whiner, but that is 
no reason to treat her so roughly.

183
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:54,860
That's right!

184
00:16:56,950 --> 00:16:58,790
I had no other choice.

185
00:17:02,360 --> 00:17:04,230
To tell you the truth...

186
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:07,700
I know about the magic called "Nirvana."

187
00:17:08,730 --> 00:17:09,930
You do?

188
00:17:11,150 --> 00:17:14,800
But I couldn't tell anyone its true nature.

189
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:18,390
This magic is very dangerous when 
you know about it consciously.

190
00:17:20,260 --> 00:17:23,760
That's why Ichiya-san and 
even Ren and Eve don't know.

191
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:26,600
Only I was told by the Master.

192
00:17:26,600 --> 00:17:27,900
What do you mean?

193
00:17:27,900 --> 00:17:30,820
It's an extremely fearsome magic.

194
00:17:32,290 --> 00:17:34,430
It switches light for darkness.

195
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:36,850
That's Nirvana...

196
00:17:37,500 --> 00:17:39,980
Light and darkness?

197
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:41,170
It switches them?

198
00:17:41,770 --> 00:17:44,120
That's the final stage.

199
00:17:44,630 --> 00:17:48,180
When the seal is first released, 
black light rises up.

200
00:17:48,180 --> 00:17:50,080
Just like that light.

201
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:51,790
First there's the black light...

202
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:57,000
The people in between the light and the 
darkness switch to the opposite element.

203
00:18:01,140 --> 00:18:03,810
The people of light who feel 
powerful negative emotion...

204
00:18:06,790 --> 00:18:08,250
...fall into darkness.

205
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:13,270
Then the reason you put Wendy to sleep was...

206
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:18,240
It's my fault! It's because I healed Jellal!

207
00:18:19,250 --> 00:18:22,030
Feeling guilt is a negative emotion, see...

208
00:18:22,350 --> 00:18:26,060
At that rate, Wendy-chan might 
have fallen into darkness.

209
00:18:26,060 --> 00:18:29,580
Wait a moment. Then, what about anger?

210
00:18:31,290 --> 00:18:33,170
Natsu's in trouble!

211
00:18:35,330 --> 00:18:37,100
I can't really say.

212
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:42,020
If that anger is for someone else's sake, I 
wouldn't necessarily call it a negative emotion...

213
00:18:43,680 --> 00:18:46,950
What'll we do? I don't understand!

214
00:18:46,950 --> 00:18:48,310
That's because you're an idiot.

215
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:52,670
In other words, when the 
seal on Nirvana is lifted,

216
00:18:52,670 --> 00:18:55,360
those who are motivated by justice or evil

217
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:58,080
have their personality switched, right?

218
00:18:58,750 --> 00:19:02,700
That's why I kept silent about 
the type of magic it was!

219
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:09,110
When people become focused on 
the good and evil of things,

220
00:19:09,110 --> 00:19:11,660
it gives rise to unimaginable 
negative emotions.

221
00:19:13,570 --> 00:19:15,210
"If it wasn't for him..."

222
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:18,030
"Whose fault is it that I suffer like this?"

223
00:19:19,080 --> 00:19:20,650
"Why is it always me?"

224
00:19:21,010 --> 00:19:25,750
Those thoughts will all be judged by Nirvana.

225
00:19:26,510 --> 00:19:27,180
What the...

226
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:46,630
I have attacked the enemy, Lyon-sama.

227
00:19:46,630 --> 00:19:48,310
Who is next?

228
00:19:48,630 --> 00:19:52,610
His friends, Fairy Tail?

229
00:19:54,830 --> 00:19:57,340
Money! Money! Money! Money!

230
00:19:57,340 --> 00:19:59,750
What are you saying?

231
00:19:59,750 --> 00:20:03,180
Money!

232
00:20:04,110 --> 00:20:06,020
...I have no need for such a thing.

233
00:20:06,020 --> 00:20:07,350
Yes.

234
00:20:09,930 --> 00:20:14,130
I've been all frantic about 
my long-lost brother!

235
00:20:14,610 --> 00:20:18,050
I thought... If only I had 
money, I could find him!

236
00:20:18,050 --> 00:20:19,320
Yes.

237
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:23,550
But I have realized, I took it too far!

238
00:20:24,220 --> 00:20:25,370
Yes.

239
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:29,270
So, I have decided to no longer fight!

240
00:20:29,760 --> 00:20:30,740
Yes.

241
00:20:30,740 --> 00:20:34,430
I will fill the world with love! Yes, love!

242
00:20:34,430 --> 00:20:37,960
A word that just overflows 
with sweetness and compassion!

243
00:20:37,960 --> 00:20:41,670
As long as there is love in this 
world, nothing is impossible!

244
00:20:41,670 --> 00:20:42,670
Yes.

245
00:20:42,670 --> 00:20:47,350
Now, let us stop the violent 
acts of my former allies!

246
00:20:47,700 --> 00:20:50,940
I shall teach them the wonders of love!

247
00:20:50,940 --> 00:20:51,890
Yes.

248
00:20:52,330 --> 00:20:54,950
Um...

249
00:20:58,640 --> 00:20:59,940
White Fury!

250
00:21:13,800 --> 00:21:15,830
The hunt has started.

251
00:21:15,830 --> 00:21:18,710
Who the hell is this guy?

252
00:21:19,350 --> 00:21:21,100
My magic won't hit...

253
00:21:23,590 --> 00:21:26,410
Oh? Still alive?

254
00:21:31,110 --> 00:21:33,520
I'm not a nice guy.

255
00:21:34,730 --> 00:21:39,730
So if Nirvana fully activates, 
we'll all become bad guys?

256
00:21:39,980 --> 00:21:45,990
But in that case, wouldn't the people 
from the Dark Guilds turn into good guys?

257
00:21:45,990 --> 00:21:48,250
I suppose that is possible.

258
00:21:48,600 --> 00:21:53,620
But the truly fearsome power of Nirvana 
lies in the ability to control it that way.

259
00:21:54,970 --> 00:21:59,210
For example, if you used 
Nirvana against a guild...

260
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:03,870
The allies could kill each 
other without hesitation.

261
00:22:03,870 --> 00:22:06,210
They could go to war with 
other guilds for no reason.

262
00:22:06,210 --> 00:22:08,460
Starting things like that 
would be child's play.

263
00:22:08,460 --> 00:22:09,570
Oh, no!

264
00:22:10,270 --> 00:22:12,450
We have to stop it at once!

265
00:22:16,300 --> 00:22:19,000
They're going to wipe out 
all the light guilds!

266
00:23:55,630 --> 00:23:58,450
Natsu... I think you'd be red.

267
00:23:58,450 --> 00:24:00,130
Huh? What're you talkin' about?

268
00:24:00,130 --> 00:24:02,020
The color that fits your image!

269
00:24:02,020 --> 00:24:04,330
You use flames, so you're red.

270
00:24:04,330 --> 00:24:07,250
Gray uses ice, so I guess 
that makes him blue.

271
00:24:07,250 --> 00:24:10,920
Happy... You're givin' away your own color?

272
00:24:10,920 --> 00:24:14,160
Y-You're right! W-What'll I do?

273
00:24:14,160 --> 00:24:16,500
Next time: Spirit vs. Spirit!

274
00:24:16,500 --> 00:24:19,100
Then how about I be 
something cool like black?

275
00:24:19,100 --> 00:24:20,100
No... Black is totally Lucy.

276
00:24:20,370 --> 00:24:23,880
She's definitely got the blackest 
personality in Fairy Tail!

277
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:26,130


